Title: _app.admin.integrations._index page
Route file: web/routes/_app.admin.integrations._index.tsx
Suggested path: /app/admin/integrations

Role/Purpose
- Provide centralized registry of all integrations (marketplaces, couriers, printers) with health monitoring, credential management, and webhook status.
- Enable administrators to monitor integration health, track credential rotation schedules, and identify webhook failures.

Primary UI Components
- `PageHeader` with title "Integrations" and description.
- Summary metric cards showing: Live connections count, Needs attention count, Credentials due count, Webhook alerts count.
- Type filter `Select` (All, Marketplace, Courier, Printing).
- Custom `Table` component from `@/components/ui/table` listing integrations with columns: Provider, Type, Status, Mode, Last sync, Credentials, Webhooks.
- Expandable rows showing credential details (env, status, expiration) and webhook endpoints (url, status, last event).
- Status badges with icons and color coding (connected=emerald, degraded=amber, requires_action=orange, disconnected=rose).
- Optional error `Alert` when using fallback data.

Data Dependencies
- Loader calls optional `context.api.integration.findMany()` with nested selects for `integrationCredentials` and `webhookEndpoints`.
- Selects: `id`, `provider`, `label`, `type`, `status`, `createdAt`, `updatedAt`, `metadata`, `scopes`, nested credentials and webhooks.
- If integration model unavailable or query fails, returns `FALLBACK_INTEGRATIONS` array (3 curated records: Shopify, Amazon, FedEx, Printful) with `source: "fallback"` and `error` message.
- Computes summary metrics from integration records: live connections, needs attention (status !== "connected"), credentials due (rotation_due/expired), webhook alerts (failing/paused).

